At least seven people were injured after a gas tanker exploded at Bolek Petrol Filling Station, opposite the Benue State University (BSU)â€™s College of Health Sciences in Makurdi Monday evening. Daily Trust gathered that the tanker exploded around 6:10pm just few minutes after it discharged gas at the station. It was learnt that the victims of the explosion included two workers of the fuel station, two undergraduates of BSU and three others. The victims were said to be immediately rushed to the Benue State University Teaching Hospital (BSUTH) where they are currently receiving medical attention. A manager of the fuel station, John Ekpo, told newsmen that the gas tanker was negotiating to exit the premises of the station after discharging its content when it suddenly exploded. A female victim, Pastor Jude Ochife, had her two legs burnt. Seven injured in Benue gas tanker explosion Petrol tanker explodes close to INEC office in Jos UPDATE: Petroleum tanker falls in Gombe